The woman was found in possession of 46 Sassa cards, 49 ID books and at least R13,000 in cash. JOHANNESBURG A loan shark has been arrested in the Roodepoort CBD while trying to withdraw money from the ATM.She was found in possession of 46 Sassa cards, 49 ID books and at least R13,000 in cash.The woman is expected to appear at the Roodepoort Magistrates Court on Monday for illegal business and possession of cards that don t belong to her.Sassa spokesperson Nandi Mosia says they are urging the public to be vigilant and keep their Sassa cards and pin numbers safe. The woman was arrested immediately and will appear in court on Monday on possession of cards that don t belong to her. 